"""Tests for v2 process derivation under PID reuse.

A PID can be reassigned by the OS to a new Claude process after the prior
owner dies. The v2 design (docs/design/api.md) says reuse must produce a
distinct process_id (different earliest_received_at). The whole derivation
layer must split a tuple's history at each claude_log_pid_deaths.observed_at
into separate "instance windows" and treat each instance as its own process.

Each test sets up a small reuse scenario and pins one specific behavior.
"""

from pathlib import Path
from unittest.mock import patch

